When a sudden change like introducing then removing a potential occurs over very short timescales compared to natural oscillation periods, we consider transitions due to Fermi’s Golden Rule involving transition probabilities proportional to squared absolute value of overlap integrals of initial and final states weighted by interaction strength and duration.

